vulnerability.name: USN-6719-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6719-1 fixed a vulnerability in util-linux. Unfortunately, it was discovered that the fix did not fully address the issue. This update removes the setgid permission bit from the wall and write utilities.  Original advisory details:   Skyler Ferrante discovered that the util-linux wall command did not filter  escape sequences from command line arguments. A local attacker could  possibly use this issue to obtain sensitive information.

statements.status_notes: util-linux could be made to expose sensitive information.
